cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.RO, cs.CG, cs.MM 

The paper deals with the reconstruction and calibration of 3D curves from multiple views, which is a problem in computer vision and graphics. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves geometric and algebraic concepts, which suggests that it could belong to cs.GR (Graphics) or cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The use of camera estimation and tracking implies that it could also be relevant to cs.RO (Robotics and Control). Finally, the paper mentions the reconstruction of 3D curve sketches, which could be related to cs.MM (Multimedia).
